begin_memory_text: We introduced ourselves, and then we talked about the cities we lived in and what the areas were like. We talked about the weather and the crime in our cities.
middle_memory_text: We started talking about the coronavirus and the affects it has had on us. I learned that my partner had gotten the virus and was hospitalized for 5 days from it. We talked about the effects it has had on our lives.
end_memory_text: We talked some more about the coronavirus and the impacts it has had on her life, and the precautions we have taken. We talked a little about the medications she was on to treat her current condition. We briefly talked about politics.
rest_of_day_open: I see the rest of my week as being a little hectic tomorrow as I have some projects to complete before the weekend for work. This weekend I plan on enjoying some time with my family and doing something interesting with them that we all can enjoy. I see it as a calm, quiet last few days after I get through tomorrow.
critical_positive: We both wanted to carry on a conversation so bringing up subjects was fairly easy and we were able to talk about a variety of subjects. The interest from the both of us to get to know somebody new helped, and we were both alert and ready to engage in conversation. Being open minded helped a lot to get through this conversation.
critical_negative: Not knowing a lot about each other played a part in not knowing what direction our conversation was going to go. I was a little cautious at times in my talking as I didn't want to offend her, as I knew she was struggling with medical issues. I had to be careful in finding subjects to discuss with her to not offend her.

begin_memory_text: I think we talked about the weather in our respective cities. Mine was cold and rainy and his was warm and rainy. We also talked about the crime rates in our cities also.
middle_memory_text: We talked about how each of our cities has a professional football team and how small Green Bay is to be able to support one. I told him how much it messes up traffic during game days.
end_memory_text: We talked about how we are each staying safe from Covid and how I ended up getting it from my mom despite not leaving my house. We talked about shopping online. How his kids were in online school.
rest_of_day_open: The rest of this week I get to relax. I’m going to fill out my ballot and drop it off, get gas in my car and buy some new tires. I’ll watch the new episode of Star Trek and have a good weekend. It should be pretty chill.  I’ll also play some animal crossing.
critical_positive: Despite our age difference we were able to find lots in common. We talked about politics without talking about which party we were for. We talked well past the 25 minutes we were supposed to because we were have such a good conversation. We had things in common that were surprising.
critical_negative: At times I had a second that I couldn’t figure out what to talk about next. I really liked him. I was apprehensive for about 30 seconds because he was so much older than me but it went great. I can’t think of anything else that didn’t work well. I really enjoy this.
